id: pm-7rlp
title: "CI/CD + test-suite performance: in-process CLI runner and dedupe redundant matrix legs"
description: "CI/test audit. Biggest win: ~1,500+ real 'node dist/cli.js' subprocess spawns dominate the 1414-test suite (742 runCli sites + 757 withTempPmPath inits; cold spawn ~35-44ms each). Add an in-process runner that calls main(argv) directly (capture stdout/stderr, reset module state), keep a small set of true-subprocess E2E tests; convert help-runtime + release-readiness + the bulk of unit specs. CI: the full suite runs 2-4x per run because build-test matrix legs run 'pnpm test' while gates(coverage) runs the same suite + coverage; on PR/push run ubuntu-20 coverage as authoritative and move the OS x Node compat matrix to nightly only; dedupe 'npm pack --dry-run' between static and smokes. Keep the 100% coverage gate. Free GitHub features only. Auto-release change-detection was audited and is CORRECT (no bug)."
type: Chore
status: in_progress
priority: 1
tags[3]: ci,performance,tests
created_at: "2026-05-21T21:57:10.762Z"
updated_at: "2026-05-25T12:47:13.642Z"
assignee: codex-reliability-history-agent
author: claude-code-agent
acceptance_criteria: Suite wall-time cut substantially via in-process runner; CI removes redundant full-suite legs; 100% coverage gate intact; nightly retains full OS/Node matrix.
parent: pm-rnpb
comments[26]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-05-23T15:58:16.337Z",codex-active-work,"Implementation update: CI workflow now avoids running pnpm test in the PR/push runtime matrix; coverage remains the authoritative full-suite gate on Ubuntu Node 20, while the runtime matrix verifies the built dist artifact across Ubuntu/macOS and Node 20/22/24. Nightly keeps the full OS/Node test matrix. Updated ci-workflow contract coverage accordingly."
  "2026-05-23T15:58:30.136Z",codex-observability-verifier,"Privacy/observability verifier evidence (2026-05-23):\n\nOrientation (read-only):\n- `pm context --limit 10` -> active parent `pm-rnpb` in_progress; active child `pm-7rlp` in_progress.\n- `pm search \"pm-7rlp privacy observability telemetry sentry secret\" --limit 10` -> reused canonical `pm-rnpb`/`pm-7rlp`; no duplicate item created.\n- `pm list-in-progress --limit 20` -> only `pm-rnpb` and `pm-7rlp` in progress.\n\nBootstrap/surface checks:\n- `command -v pm && pm --version && node -v && pnpm -v` -> pm resolved on PATH, version 2026.5.23; Node v25.9.0; pnpm 10.33.0.\n- Preferred full release/observability gate identified from `package.json` and `scripts/release/run-gates.mjs`: `node scripts/release/run-gates.mjs --telemetry-mode best-effort` via npm script `release:gates`; the full gate includes secret scan, build/static/test/dogfood work, and delegates Sentry/telemetry to `scripts/release/sentry-telemetry-gate.mjs`. For this read-only verifier lane, I ran the compact delegated gate directly instead of the full release gate.\n\nSafe verification commands/results:\n- `node scripts/check-secrets.mjs` -> PASS: \"No credential-like secrets detected in tracked files.\" Privacy note: this is the tracked-file secret gate; it does not prove append-only history streams are free of historical sensitive text. Existing history-redaction lineage remains `pm-xk39`.\n- `pm health --check-only --brief --json` -> PASS: `ok=true`, warnings `[]`; telemetry enabled with redacted capture, endpoint `https://pm-cli.unbrained.dev/v1/events`, queue_exists=true, queue_entries=6, queue_draining=true, queue_invalid_rows=0, queue_rows_total=6, last_successful_flush_at=2026-05-23T15:57:41.391Z, last_failed_flush_at=null; extensions/storage/integrity/history_drift/vectorization all reported ok in brief projection.\n- `node scripts/release/sentry-telemetry-gate.mjs --json --telemetry-mode required --max-critical 10 --max-high 20 --max-telemetry-error-rate 10 --max-telemetry-missing-error-rows 0` -> PASS: `ok=true`; Sentry checked=true, token_source reported as `SENTRY_PERSONAL_ADMIN_TOKEN` (token value not printed), critical=0, high=0, total=0, access_ok=true, threshold_ok=true; telemetry checked=true, mode=required, ok=true, finish_error_rate_pct=2.75, failures_without_error_code_rows=0.\n\nPrivacy findings:\n- No credential-like secrets were found in tracked files by the tracked-tree scanner.\n- No secret values were printed or recorded; only environment variable names and redacted/aggregate observability outputs are included.\n- Compact health output shows redacted telemetry capture and no failed flush.\n- Live Sentry/telemetry gate passed with maintained thresholds and no current Sentry issues returned for the project."
  "2026-05-23T15:58:42.460Z",codex-ci-test-scout,"CI/test performance scout findings (read-only pass, 2026-05-23):\n\n1) Smallest safe in-process runner implementation slice:\n- Add a new test-only in-process runner path next to tests/helpers/withTempPmPath.ts, not in production command code. Keep the existing runCli contract (code/stdout/stderr/json) and add an opt-in runner mode first, e.g. runCliInProcess or withTempPmPath({ runner: 'in-process' }), so existing subprocess behavior remains the default until proven.\n- Production CLI needs a narrow seam before this can be safe: src/cli/main.ts currently computes bootstrapInvocation from process.argv at module load, owns a singleton Commander program, mutates process.exitCode, and executes void main() immediately. The safe slice is to export a function such as runPmCli(argv, { cwd, env, stdin, stdout, stderr }) from a new internal entry module, have src/cli.ts call that wrapper for the real binary, and let tests call the function directly. Do not import src/cli.ts or dist/cli.js in-process because they are executable entrypoints with process.argv/module-load side effects.\n- The test harness should capture output by injecting/wrapping the existing output layer or temporary writable streams, snapshot and restore process.cwd/process.env/process.exitCode, reset singleton command/extension/telemetry state between invocations, and keep the legacy create-arg normalization in one place so converted tests do not drift from current fixture behavior.\n- Convert in layers: start with help-runtime and low-risk unit command specs that use context.runCli for JSON/status assertions, then migrate the bulk of release-readiness-runtime's help/runtime matrix and unit specs with many create/get/history/list calls. The largest payoff files from current counts are tests/integration/cli.integration.spec.ts (~312 runCli sites), tests/integration/release-readiness-runtime.spec.ts (~113), tests/integration/help-runtime.spec.ts (~56), then unit fixtures such as beads/todos/restore/get-append/history/activity/templates/validate.\n- Acceptance for the first slice: keep one subprocess parity spec that runs a representative set through both paths (success JSON, usage error, not-found error, help, extension-installed command) and prove the in-process path preserves code/stdout/stderr/json semantics before broad migration.\n\n2) Tests that should remain true subprocess E2E:\n- Entry/bootstrap behavior: --version/-V fast path, src/cli.ts/dist/cli.js shebang/compile-cache path, package bin/export contract, and any test asserting node dist/cli.js behavior.\n- Shell/process semantics: EPIPE/broken pipe coverage, bash wildcard expansion around install '*', stdin piping, cwd/env isolation that depends on a fresh process, FORCE_COLOR/no-color output, signal/timeout behavior, and any command intentionally run through bash/sh.\n- Runner/CI contracts: tests/integration/run-tests-script.integration.spec.ts must keep spawning scripts/run-tests.mjs because it validates argument forwarding and sandbox env; release automation script help/pipeline tests that spawn node scripts should also stay subprocess; ci-workflow-contract remains file-based.\n- Extension/plugin process boundaries: tests that validate process-spawn permissions, external git/npm/tar invocation, background test-run workers, plugin smoke scripts, npx/package smoke, and linked-test execution should stay subprocess where process behavior is the feature.\n- Cross-owner conflict or fresh-process global-state checks can be selectively left subprocess until the in-process reset hooks have proven no leakage.\n\n3) Exact CI dedupe recommendation using only free GitHub features:\n- Keep GitHub Actions only; no paid services required. Use workflow matrices, needs/artifacts, paths-ignore, concurrency cancel-in-progress, and the existing actions/cache/upload-artifact/download-artifact setup.\n- Make the Ubuntu Node 20 coverage gate the authoritative full-suite run on PR and push. Remove the duplicate full pnpm test pass from PR/push build-test legs; keep only a quick dist smoke on ubuntu-20 plus focused OS smoke commands on macOS Node 20 if desired. Full OS/Node matrix test coverage belongs in nightly.yml.\n- For main pushes, avoid re-running the entire suite on ubuntu Node 22/24 when nightly already covers Node 20/22/24/25 plus macOS/windows. Main should keep build-foundation, coverage, typecheck, static, compat, and smokes; nightly should remain the broad compatibility net.\n- Deduplicate npm pack --dry-run: ci.yml currently runs it in the static gate while smoke:npx also packages from the workspace. Pick one authoritative packaging check per workflow, preferably static for raw npm pack contract and smokes for install/use behavior, but do not package twice unless a comment explains distinct assertions.\n- Keep the existing docs paths-ignore on push and the workflow contract spec updated with the intended reduced shape so CI topology regressions are caught in tests.\n\n4) Risks:\n- src/cli/main.ts is not currently reentrant: bootstrap argv is captured at module load, Commander and extension descriptor state are module singletons, and command handlers mutate process.exitCode/process.env/global services. A naive direct import would create order-dependent test failures and false confidence.\n- Output capture can hide broken-pipe, color, TTY, pager, and stderr/stdout routing regressions; these need subprocess parity coverage.\n- Extension loading and telemetry/Sentry hooks have global state and after-command hooks; in-process tests must provide explicit reset hooks or run in serial for migrated cases.\n- CI dedupe reduces PR signal breadth. The mitigation is to keep coverage/typecheck/static/compat/smokes on PR/push and preserve nightly as the full OS/Node compatibility matrix, with branch protection requiring the reduced PR gates only.\n- Existing workflow contract tests are intentionally string-specific, so any CI topology change must update tests/integration/ci-workflow-contract.spec.ts in the same patch.\n\nInspected: tests/helpers/withTempPmPath.ts, scripts/run-tests.mjs, package.json scripts, .github/workflows/ci.yml, .github/workflows/nightly.yml, vitest.config.ts, src/cli.ts, src/cli/main.ts, tests/integration/cli.integration.spec.ts, tests/integration/release-readiness-runtime.spec.ts, tests/integration/help-runtime.spec.ts, tests/integration/run-tests-script.integration.spec.ts, tests/integration/ci-workflow-contract.spec.ts, tests/integration/release-automation-contract.spec.ts, tests/integration/governance-presets.integration.spec.ts, tests/unit/extension-command.spec.ts, and runCli usage counts across tests/."
  "2026-05-23T15:59:38.036Z",codex-active-work,"Decision: implementing the CI dedupe portion of pm-7rlp in this PR and intentionally leaving the in-process runner conversion open for a follow-up slice. Sub-agent scout confirmed the runner needs a production CLI reentrancy seam first because src/cli/main.ts currently captures argv at module load, owns singleton Commander/extension state, mutates process.exitCode, and runs main immediately. A naive direct import would risk order-dependent false positives. Current branch keeps the safe CI win: PR/push full-suite duplication removed, coverage remains authoritative, nightly keeps OS/Node full-suite coverage."
  "2026-05-23T16:06:46.152Z",codex-active-work,"Verification note: first linked pm test run passed package-first dogfood and the workflow contract test, but the full release gate failed only inside pm test's schema sandbox during smoke:npx with a calendar read warning. Direct smoke:npx passed immediately afterward from the real checkout. Rerunning the linked suite with --shared-host-safe because the release gate packages the real checkout and performs nested npx/npm temp-project smokes; sandboxing that command can introduce unrelated tracker fixture state."
  "2026-05-23T16:11:51.195Z",codex-active-work,"Linked-test adjustment: replaced the release-gate command with an env-cleared form () so pm test does not inject its schema sandbox into a gate that intentionally packages and smokes the checkout. This keeps the command reproducible through pm while matching how CI and direct release gates run."
  "2026-05-23T16:11:58.322Z",codex-active-work,"Correction to prior note: the env-cleared linked release gate command is: env -u PM_PATH -u PM_GLOBAL_PATH node scripts/release/run-gates.mjs --telemetry-mode required --max-sentry-critical 10 --max-sentry-high 20 --max-telemetry-error-rate 10 --json."
  "2026-05-23T16:20:43.996Z",codex-active-work,"Full release gate evidence: direct checkout run passed after CI dedupe changes. Command: node scripts/release/run-gates.mjs --telemetry-mode required --max-sentry-critical 10 --max-sentry-high 20 --max-telemetry-error-rate 10 --json. Results: build/typecheck/docs/static/coverage/version/security/npx-smoke/package-first-dogfood/npm-pack/compatibility all ok; coverage 102 files / 1528 tests / 100% statements branches functions lines; Sentry critical=0 high=0 total=0; telemetry finish_error_rate_pct=2.7 and failures_without_error_code_rows=0. The full gate is intentionally recorded as direct evidence rather than a linked pm test because pm test's schema sandbox consistently perturbs the nested npx smoke PM context while the same gate passes in the real checkout and CI context."
  "2026-05-23T16:21:57.487Z",codex-active-work,"Final local evidence before PR: manual temp-project walkthrough passed in isolated PM_PATH/PM_GLOBAL_PATH covering init --with-packages, create/claim/update, files/docs/comments/notes/learnings, linked test run, list/context/search/contracts, history --verify, validate, health, close, and release. Linked pm tests now pass: node scripts/dogfood-package-first.mjs and node scripts/run-tests.mjs test -- tests/integration/ci-workflow-contract.spec.ts. Direct full release gate passed with required Sentry/telemetry. Tracker hygiene passed: pm validate --check-resolution --check-history-drift ok with no warnings; pm health --check-only --brief ok with no warnings; tracked secret scan clean."
  "2026-05-23T16:22:39.818Z",codex-active-work,"PR evidence: pushed commit 37846e96 on branch codex/ci-runtime-smoke-dedupe and opened PR #50, Deduplicate CI full-suite matrix into runtime smoke: https://github.com/unbraind/pm-cli/pull/50. Starting required >=15 minute AI-review wait and GitHub check watch before merge."
  "2026-05-23T16:31:42.552Z",codex-ci-runtime-smoke,"PR #50 AI review response: applied the valid CodeRabbit/Gemini feedback by trimming Runtime smoke setup to checkout + Node + dist download + version smoke only, removing pnpm/cache/install work from the extra runtime legs, and strengthening tests/integration/ci-workflow-contract.spec.ts to assert the exact runtime matrix and block pnpm/cache/test steps inside build-test. Reviewed .agents/pm direct-edit comments as false positives: all tracker mutations in this run were performed through pm CLI commands, and prior validate/history checks were clean. Verification after review fix: pnpm build && node scripts/run-tests.mjs test -- tests/integration/ci-workflow-contract.spec.ts passed."
  "2026-05-23T16:32:27.062Z",codex-ci-runtime-smoke,"Post-review observability evidence: node scripts/check-secrets.mjs passed with no credential-like secrets in tracked files; pm validate --check-resolution --check-history-drift --json passed with no warnings; pm health --check-only --brief --json initially showed only freshly queued telemetry rows, then passed clean after queue drain with last_successful_flush_at=2026-05-23T16:31:58.535Z and no warnings; node scripts/release/sentry-telemetry-gate.mjs --json --telemetry-mode required --max-critical 10 --max-high 20 --max-telemetry-error-rate 10 --max-telemetry-missing-error-rows 0 passed with Sentry critical=0 high=0 total=0 and telemetry finish_error_rate_pct=2.69, missing error-code rows=0."
  "2026-05-23T16:39:44.602Z",codex-ci-runtime-smoke,"Final AI review cleanup: applied remaining Gemini robustness suggestion by replacing the literal LF assertion for absent pnpm test steps with a multiline regex assertion in tests/integration/ci-workflow-contract.spec.ts. Re-ran pnpm build && node scripts/run-tests.mjs test -- tests/integration/ci-workflow-contract.spec.ts; passed."
  "2026-05-23T16:47:14.852Z",codex-ci-runtime-smoke,"Merge evidence: PR #50 was squash-merged into main as d7b983d2187a0b53fadc48900c94d5a6e45a81c0 after the required >=15 minute AI-review window. Latest PR checks were green on commit a8cc3555: Build foundation, Runtime smoke ubuntu Node 20, Runtime smoke macOS Node 20, Runtime smoke ubuntu Node 22, Runtime smoke ubuntu Node 24, Gates coverage/typecheck/static/compat/smokes, CodeRabbit, and Sourcery. pm-7rlp remains open because the safe in-process runner work requires a separate CLI reentrancy slice; this merged slice completed the CI dedupe/runtime-smoke portion."
  "2026-05-25T08:43:00.433Z",codex-dedupe-agent,"Implementation note: folded fresh GitHub Nightly Windows failure into this PR after duplicate search found pm-7rlp as canonical CI/test reliability item. Fixing npm.cmd resolution for Windows packed-package tests, CRLF-tolerant generated runtime-loader drift checks, and executable release-pipeline import avoidance via a pure release-relevance helper."
  "2026-05-25T08:56:50.667Z",codex-dedupe-agent,"Verification evidence for Windows Nightly reliability slice: focused regression suite passed including package-manifest/check-secrets/release automation/CLI coverage; full release gate passed with coverage/static/security/package dogfood/compatibility/observability. The branch now uses npm.cmd on Windows for npm pack, CRLF-tolerant generated runtime loader checks, and a pure release-relevance helper to avoid importing executable release pipeline code in tests."
  "2026-05-25T09:00:17.454Z",codex-dedupe-agent,"Implementation note: split secret scanner reusable rules into scripts/check-secrets-lib.mjs so Vitest imports a plain library module on Windows while scripts/check-secrets.mjs remains the executable CLI wrapper. Focused verification passed: node scripts/run-tests.mjs test -- tests/unit/check-secrets.spec.ts tests/integration/release-automation-contract.spec.ts tests/integration/release-readiness-runtime.spec.ts -t 'keeps release-hardening scaffolding paths present|check-secrets|Auto Release' --reporter=dot (2 files passed, 1 skipped, 7 tests passed, 42 skipped) and node scripts/check-secrets.mjs reported no credential-like secrets."
